When the sun cast long shadows over the rake grass, Im Chaem refused to talk about his past in the Red Jemers.
She claimed that if the court called her, she wouldn't introduce herself.
"Cambodia is at peace and stable," he said.
"If there are more trials, there will be war."
Prime Minister Hun Sen, who deserted the Red Jemers in 1978, has also repeatedly warned that there will be instability if the court pursues more suspects, although experts and historians question it.
"Cambodia must dig a hole and bury the past," he said.
